TrustZone_initialize
├── when already initialized
│   └── it should revert with AlreadyInitialized
└── when not yet initialized
    ├── it should store the hatValidator address
    ├── it should install HatValidator as validator module (type 1)
    ├── it should install agreement contract as executor module (type 2)
    ├── it should install HookMultiPlexer as hook module (type 4)
    └── it should emit TrustZoneInitialized

TrustZone_hatValidator
├── given not yet initialized
│   └── it should return address(0)
└── given initialized
    └── it should return the hatValidator address passed to initialize

TrustZone_checkEntryPointOrSelf
├── when caller is the entryPoint
│   └── it should not revert
├── when caller is address(this)
│   └── it should not revert
├── when caller wears the hat (via HatValidator.isAuthorized)
│   └── it should not revert
└── when caller is none of the above
    └── it should revert with Unauthorized

TrustZone_execute_convenience
├── when caller is the entryPoint
│   ├── it should execute the call on the target
│   └── it should run hooks (preCheck + postCheck)
├── when caller wears the hat
│   ├── it should execute the call on the target
│   ├── it should forward the ETH value
│   └── it should run hooks (preCheck + postCheck)
└── when caller is not authorized
    └── it should revert with Unauthorized

TrustZone_execute_7579
├── when caller is the entryPoint
│   ├── given mode is single call
│   │   ├── it should execute the call
│   │   └── it should run hooks
│   └── given mode is batch call
│       ├── it should execute all calls
│       └── it should run hooks for each call
├── when caller wears the hat
│   └── it should execute the call
└── when caller is not authorized
    └── it should revert with Unauthorized

TrustZone_executeFromExecutor
├── when caller is not an installed executor module
│   └── it should revert
└── when caller is an installed executor module
    └── it should execute the call as the TrustZone

TrustZone_isValidSignature
├── given no validator is installed
│   └── it should return failure magic value
└── given HatValidator is installed
    ├── when signer wears the hat
    │   └── it should return 0x1626ba7e (ERC-1271 magic value)
    └── when signer does not wear the hat
        └── it should return failure magic value
